\begin_layout Standard
The Small Magellanic Cloud (SMC) is a nearby dwarf irregular galaxy with
 a gas rich interstellar medium (ISM).
 As a member of a three galaxy system, the Large Magellanic Cloud, Small
 Magellanic Cloud, and the Milky Way, the SMC has undergone interactions
 which have resulted in an extended envolope of neutral gas
